-------------------------------------------------------------------------React Router DOM-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

React Router DOM is a library used in React applications to create multiple pages and navigate between them without reloading the browser. It helps build single-page applications (SPAs) with smooth and fast navigation.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

---------------------------------------------------------------------Why React Router DOM is used----------------------------------------------------------

(1) To create multi-page navigation in React apps.
(2) To change the URL without refreshing the page.
(3) To manage browser history (back and forward buttons work).
(4) To load different components based on the URL path.

Installation
npm install react-router-dom

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Main Components and Hooks

1. BrowserRouter

Wraps the app and enables routing.

<BrowserRouter>
  <App />
</BrowserRouter>

2. Routes and Route

Define which component should show for each URL.

<Routes>
  <Route path="/" element={<Home />} />
  <Route path="/about" element={<About />} />
</Routes>

3. Link

Used for navigation without reloading the page.

<Link to="/about">About</Link>

4. useNavigate

Allows navigation using functions.

const navigate = useNavigate();
navigate("/login");

5. useParams

Reads dynamic route parameters.

Example: /user/10

const { id } = useParams();

6. NavLink

Similar to Link but shows active styling.

7. Nested Routes

Allows layouts with multiple pages inside a main route.

<Route path="/dashboard" element={<Dashboard />}>
  <Route path="profile" element={<Profile />} />
</Route>

Additional Concepts
Redirects
<Navigate to="/login" />

Not Found Route
<Route path="*" element={<NotFound />} />

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Key Points

1.Route components must be inside <Routes>.
2.React Router DOM v6 uses element={<Component />} instead of component={}.
3.Switch has been replaced by Routes.
4.useHistory has been replaced by useNavigate.